cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is about learning computational models for visual attention (saliency estimation) using deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the design choices in architecture, which suggests it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes novel end-to-end architectures, which could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions real-time applications, which could suggest it belongs to cs.RO (Robotics).
